    return f'../data/processed/or{orient}pix{pixels}cell{cells}{bf}'

In [8]:
# test una imagen
def hog_img_full(img_id, orientation, pixels_per_cell, cells_per_block):
    img = Image.open(f'{raw_dir}/{img_id}')
    start = time.time()
    fd, hoggedImg = hog(img, orientations=orientation, pixels_per_cell=(pixels_per_cell, pixels_per_cell), cells_per_block=(cells_per_block, cells_per_block), visualize=True)
    end = time.time()
    img.close()
    print(f'Orientation {orientation}')
    print(f'pixels_per_cell {pixels_per_cell}x{pixels_per_cell}')
    print(f'cells_per_block {cells_per_block}')
    print(round(end-start, 2), "segundos")
    return Image.fromarray(numpy.uint8(cm.gist_earth(hoggedImg)*255))

# test una imagen
def hog_img(img_id, orientation, pixels_per_cell, cells_per_block):
    img = Image.open(f'{raw_128_dir}/{img_id}')
    start = time.time()
    fd, hoggedImg = hog(img, orientations=orientation, pixels_per_cell=(pixels_per_cell, pixels_per_cell), cells_per_block=(cells_per_block, cells_per_block), visualize=True)
    end = time.time()
    img.close()
    print(f'Orientation {orientation}')
    print(f'pixels_per_cell {pixels_per_cell}x{pixels_per_cell}')
    print(f'cells_per_block {cells_per_block}')
    print(round(end-start, 2), "segundos")
    return Image.fromarray(numpy.uint8(cm.gist_earth(hoggedImg)*255))

In [19]:
# Aplica hog para una única imágen
def get_single_hogged_img(id, orient, pixels, cells, bilateral_filter_dir):
    img = Image.open(f'{raw_128_dir}/{bilateral_filter_dir}/{id}')
    fd, hoggedImg = hog(img, orientations=orient, pixels_per_cell=(pixels, pixels), cells_per_block=(cells, cells), visualize=True)
    img.close()
    return fd, hoggedImg

# prueba
img_test = df['image_id'][0]

In [20]:
normal = 'normal'
pneumonia = 'pneumonia'
covid = 'COVID-19'

def disease_to_num(x):
    if x == normal:
        return 0
    elif x == pneumonia:
        return 1
    elif x == covid:
        return 2
    else:
        return x

disease_to_num(df['disease'][0])

In [22]:
# Aplica hog a un conjunto de imágenes con unos determinados parámetros de hog, y guarda los resultados en un csv
def get_hogged_imgs(df, orient, pixels, cells, bf):
    features = []
    start = time.time()
    for img_id in df['image_id']:
        fd, hoggedImg = get_single_hogged_img(img_id, orient, pixels, cells, bf)
        features.append(fd)
    end = time.time()
    path = features_csv_path(orient, pixels, cells, bf)
    print('Orientation', orient, 'Pixels', pixels, 'Cells', cells, 'Time', round(end - start , 2), 'segundos', bf, path)
    np_feat = numpy.array(features)
    numpy.save(path, np_feat)

# Tarda 1 hora y media aprox
cells = [2, 4, 8]
pixels = [8, 16]
orientations = [7, 8, 9]
bilateral_filter_dirs = [bf1, bf2, bf3, bf4, bf5, bf6]

for orien in orientations:
    for pix in pixels:
        for cell in cells:
            for bf in bilateral_filter_dirs:
                get_hogged_imgs(df, orien, pix, cell, bf)

In [62]:
x = numpy.load(f'{features_csv_path(orien, pix, cell, bf1)}.npy')

clf = RandomForestClassifier(min_samples_leaf=20, random_state=seed)

scores = cross_validate(clf, X=x, y=df['disease'], cv=kfold, scoring=scoring)


print('Orientation', orien, 'Pixels', pix, 'Cells', cell, 'Bilateral Filter', bf1)
print('Recall normal:', round(scores['test_recall0'].mean(), 2))
print('Recall pneumonia:', round(scores['test_recall1'].mean(), 2))
print('Recall covid:', round(scores['test_recall2'].mean(), 2))
print('Precision normal:', round(scores['test_precision0'].mean(), 2))
print('Precision pneumonia:', round(scores['test_precision1'].mean(), 2))
print('Precision covid:', round(scores['test_precision2'].mean(), 2))

# Primer corrida sin tocar parámetros random Forest
cells = [2, 4, 8]
pixels = [8, 16]
orientations = [7, 8, 9]
billateral_filter_dirs = [bf1, bf2, bf3, bf4, bf5, bf6]

index = 0

for orien in orientations:
    for pix in pixels:
        for cell in cells:
            for bf in billateral_filter_dirs:
                start = time.time()
                x = numpy.load(f'{features_csv_path(orien, pix, cell, bf)}.npy')
                scores = cross_validate(clf, X=x, y=df['disease'], cv=kfold, scoring=scoring)
                end = time.time()
                print(f'=========================== {index} ====================================')
                print(round(end - start , 2), 'segundos')
                print('Orientation', orien, 'Pixels', pix, 'Cells', cell, 'Billateral filter', bf)
                print("Precision normal: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f)" % (scores['test_precision0'].mean(), scores['test_precision0'].std() * 2))
                print("Recall normal: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f)" % (scores['test_recall0'].mean(), scores['test_recall0'].std() * 2))
                print("Precision pneumonia: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f)" % (scores['test_precision1'].mean(), scores['test_precision1'].std() * 2))
                print("Recall pneumonia: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f)" % (scores['test_recall1'].mean(), scores['test_recall1'].std() * 2))
                print("Precision covid: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f)" % (scores['test_precision2'].mean(), scores['test_precision2'].std() * 2))
                print("Recall covid: %0.2f (+/- %0.2f) \n" % (scores['test_recall2'].mean(), scores['test_recall2'].std() * 2))
                index = index + 1

# Grid search para buscar mejores parámetros de árbol

def evaluate(model, test_features, test_labels):
    predictions = model.predict(test_features)
    errors = abs(predictions - test_labels)
    mape = 100 * np.mean(errors / test_labels)
    accuracy = 100 - mape
    print('Model Performance')
    print('Average Error: {:0.4f} degrees.'.format(np.mean(errors)))
    print('Accuracy = {:0.2f}%.'.format(accuracy))
    return accuracy


param_grid = {
    'bootstrap': [True],
    'max_depth': [80, 150, 1000],
    'max_features': [ 4, 5, 10],
    'min_samples_leaf': [10, 50, 100],
    'min_samples_split': [8, 60, 100],
    'n_estimators': [100,  500, 5000],
    'criterion': ['gini', 'entropy']
}

rf = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=seed)

clf = GridSearchCV(estimator = rf, param_grid = param_grid, cv = 3, n_jobs = -1, verbose = 2, refit=True)

cells = [2, 4, 8]
pixels = [8, 16]
orientations = [7, 8, 9]
billateral_filter_dirs = [bf1, bf2, bf3, bf4, bf5, bf6]

index = 0

for orien in orientations:
    for pix in pixels:
        for cell in cells:
            for bf in billateral_filter_dirs:
                print(f'=========================== {index} ====================================')
                print('Orientation', orien, 'Pixels', pix, 'Cells', cell, 'Billateral filter', bf)
                start = time.time()
                x = numpy.load(f'{features_csv_path(orien, pix, cell, bf)}.npy')
                X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, df['disease'], test_size=0.2, random_state=seed, stratify=df['disease'])
                clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
                print(clf.best_params_)
                y_true, y_pred = y_test, clf.predict(X_test)
                print(classification_report(y_true, y_pred))
                end = time.time()
                print(round(end - start , 2), 'segundos')
                index = index + 1

# Grid search para buscar mejores parámetros de SVM

tuned_parameters = [{'kernel': ['rbf'], 'gamma': [0.1, 0.01, 1e-3, 1e-4],
                     'C': [0.1, 1, 10, 100, 1000]},
                    {'kernel': ['linear'], 'C': [0.1, 1, 10, 100, 1000]}]

scores = ['precision']
cells = [2, 4, 8]
pixels = [8, 16]
orientations = [7, 8, 9]
billateral_filter_dirs = [bf1, bf2, bf3, bf4, bf5, bf6]
index = 0

for orien in orientations:
    for pix in pixels:
        for cell in cells:
            for bf in billateral_filter_dirs:
                for score in scores:
                    x = numpy.load(f'{features_csv_path(orien, pix, cell, bf)}.npy')
                    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, df['disease'], test_size=0.2, random_state=seed, stratify=df['disease'])
                    print(f'=========================== {index} ====================================')
                    print('Orientation', orien, 'Pixels', pix, 'Cells', cell, 'Billateral filter', bf)
                    # Split the dataset in two equal parts
                    print("# Tuning hyper-parameters for %s" % score)
                    print()

                    clf = GridSearchCV(
                        SVC(), tuned_parameters, scoring='%s_macro' % score
                    )
                    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)

                    print("Best parameters set found on development set:")
                    print()
                    print(clf.best_params_)
                    print()
                    print("Grid scores on development set:")
                    print()
                    means = clf.cv_results_['mean_test_score']
                    stds = clf.cv_results_['std_test_score']
                    for mean, std, params in zip(means, stds, clf.cv_results_['params']):
                        print("%0.3f (+/-%0.03f) for %r"
                              % (mean, std * 2, params))
                    print()

                    print("Detailed classification report:")
                    print()
                    y_true, y_pred = y_test, clf.predict(X_test)
                    print(classification_report(y_true, y_pred))
                    index = index + 1

# https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45332410/roc-for-multiclass-classification

def plot_multiclass_roc_rf(clf, X_test, y_test, n_classes, figsize=(17, 6)):
    y_score = clf.predict_proba(X_test)

    # structures
    fpr = dict()
    tpr = dict()
    roc_auc = dict()

    # calculate dummies once
    y_test_dummies = pd.get_dummies(y_test, drop_first=False).values
    for i in range(n_classes):
        fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_test_dummies[:, i], y_score[:, i])
        roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])

    # roc for each class
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)
    ax.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    ax.set_xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    ax.set_xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    ax.set_ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    ax.set_title('Receiver operating characteristic example')
    for i in range(n_classes):
        ax.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], label='ROC curve (area = %0.2f) for label %i' % (roc_auc[i], i))
    ax.legend(loc="best")
    ax.grid(alpha=.4)
    plt.show()

def plot_multiclass_roc_svm(clf, X_test, y_test, n_classes, figsize=(17, 6)):
    y_score = clf.decision_function(X_test)

    # structures
    fpr = dict()
    tpr = dict()
    roc_auc = dict()

    # calculate dummies once
    y_test_dummies = pd.get_dummies(y_test, drop_first=False).values
    for i in range(n_classes):
        fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_test_dummies[:, i], y_score[:, i])
        roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])

    # roc for each class
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)
    ax.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    ax.set_xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    ax.set_xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    ax.set_ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    ax.set_title('Receiver operating characteristic example')
    for i in range(n_classes):
        ax.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], label='ROC curve (area = %0.2f) for label %i' % (roc_auc[i], i))
    ax.legend(loc="best")
    ax.grid(alpha=.4)
    plt.show()

Corrida con los mejores parámetros de hog, bilateral filter y de cada clasificador, mostrando más estadisticas para cada uno.

rf_clf = CalibratedClassifierCV(RandomForestClassifier(
    bootstrap=True,
    criterion='gini',
    max_depth=80, 
    max_features=5, 
    min_samples_leaf=10, 
    min_samples_split=8, 
    n_estimators=5000, 
    random_state=seed
), cv=3)

print('#1 Orientation 8 Pixels 8 Cells 4 bilateral filter 1')

In [28]:
# SVM
def runSVM(orientation, pixels, cells, bfilter, svm_clf):
    print('Orientation ', orientation, 'Pixels ', pixels, 'Cells ', cells, 'Bilateral filter ', bfilter)
    x = numpy.load(f'{features_csv_path(orientation, pixels, cells, bfilter)}.npy')
    x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, df['disease'], test_size=0.1, random_state=seed, stratify=df['disease'])
    print('Classifier SVM')
    svm_clf.fit(x_train, y_train)
    y_pred = svm_clf.predict(x_test)
    precision, recall, fscore, support = precision_recall_fscore_support(y_test, y_pred)
    print('   precision: {}'.format(precision))
    print('   recall: {}'.format(recall))
    print('   fscore: {}'.format(fscore))
    print('   support: {}'.format(support))
    plot_multiclass_roc_svm(svm_clf, x_test, y_test, n_classes=3, figsize=(16, 10))
    y_pred = cross_val_predict(svm_clf, x_test, y_test, cv=10)
    print('   Matriz de confusión: ')
    print(confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred))
